# Overview

## Project Goal

This project documents the design, assembly, setup, and operation of our SatNOGS ground station.

The station is intended to:
- track satellites automatically
- receive satellite telemetry (TLE, Earth imagery, meteorological/atmospheric data)
- support educational and research activities
- provide a reproducible setup for future work

## System Summary

At a high level, the station works as follows:

Satellite signal  
→ antenna  
→ RF chain  
→ SDR  
→ Raspberry Pi running SatNOGS software

The rotator allows the antenna to follow the satellite across the sky in azimuth and elevation.

## Scope of This Repository

This repository covers:
- hardware used in the station
- software installation
- SatNOGS setup and configuration
- rotator setup
- RF chain
- testing and first observations
- troubleshooting and maintenance
